the solutions on this.

00:39:21.290 --> 00:39:22.040 align:middle line:90%
And this is important.

00:39:22.040 --> 00:39:22.840 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: Yes.

00:39:22.840 --> 00:39:25.160 align:middle line:84%
Well, I want to
first preface this

00:39:25.160 --> 00:39:27.673 align:middle line:84%
with-- sitting in that
audience in Harvard

00:39:27.673 --> 00:39:29.090 align:middle line:84%
listening to some
of my colleagues

00:39:29.090 --> 00:39:30.530 align:middle line:90%
present their science.

00:39:30.530 --> 00:39:33.440 align:middle line:84%
I presented my study, and
my science, and my work.

00:39:33.440 --> 00:39:35.600 align:middle line:84%
In listening to other
people, every one of them

00:39:35.600 --> 00:39:39.260 align:middle line:84%
had a story of
distress in childhood.

00:39:39.260 --> 00:39:42.020 align:middle line:84%
And I remember turning to
my colleague and saying,

00:39:42.020 --> 00:39:45.140 align:middle line:84%
my kids haven't had
enough to fight against.

00:39:45.140 --> 00:39:48.530 align:middle line:84%
We really try so hard
to protect our children.

00:39:48.530 --> 00:39:52.220 align:middle line:84%
I really tried hard to make
their childhood very magical.

00:39:52.220 --> 00:39:55.290 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of the day,
is that really a great thing

00:39:55.290 --> 00:39:56.090 align:middle line:90%
to do?

00:39:56.090 --> 00:39:58.795 align:middle line:84%
Are we keeping the
resistance training?

00:39:58.795 --> 00:40:00.920 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I don't want my
kids to be sexually abused.

00:40:00.920 --> 00:40:03.290 align:middle line:84%
I don't want them
to be kidnapped.

00:40:03.290 --> 00:40:06.680 align:middle line:84%
But at the end of the
day, have they had enough

00:40:06.680 --> 00:40:07.910 align:middle line:90%
to struggle against?

00:40:07.910 --> 00:40:10.010 align:middle line:84%
Because every single person
in there that had made

00:40:10.010 --> 00:40:11.630 align:middle line:84%
a giant contribution
to the world

00:40:11.630 --> 00:40:12.870 align:middle line:90%
had some kind of struggle.

00:40:12.870 --> 00:40:13.670 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Trauma.

00:40:13.670 --> 00:40:14.470 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: Yeah.

00:40:14.470 --> 00:40:17.060 align:middle line:84%
So when I do this freedom
framework, and I present it,

00:40:17.060 --> 00:40:21.222 align:middle line:84%
and I tell you about it,
I'm solving your puzzle

00:40:21.222 --> 00:40:22.430 align:middle line:90%
when I'm doing this with you.

00:40:22.430 --> 00:40:24.290 align:middle line:84%
But I'm also trying
to help you move out

00:40:24.290 --> 00:40:28.230 align:middle line:84%
of the judgment space of
that's good, that's bad.

00:40:28.230 --> 00:40:29.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Or I'm good, I'm bad.

00:40:29.480 --> 00:40:30.410 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: Exactly.

00:40:30.410 --> 00:40:32.060 align:middle line:90%
There's no good and bad food.

00:40:32.060 --> 00:40:35.510 align:middle line:84%
There's food that your body
will react to in a different way

00:40:35.510 --> 00:40:36.930 align:middle line:90%
than it will for another one.

00:40:36.930 --> 00:40:39.590 align:middle line:84%
There's also non-food
that we call food.

00:40:39.590 --> 00:40:41.270 align:middle line:84%
Anything you open
up out of a package

00:40:41.270 --> 00:40:43.220 align:middle line:84%
that you've got at the
Mini Mart is not food.

00:40:43.220 --> 00:40:45.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah, no, not anymore.

00:40:45.210 --> 00:40:46.010 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: Exactly.

00:40:46.010 --> 00:40:47.960 align:middle line:84%
And so we have to
think in those terms

00:40:47.960 --> 00:40:50.570 align:middle line:84%
when I go through the
Freedom Framework.

00:40:50.570 --> 00:40:53.090 align:middle line:84%
So the Freedom
Framework is the way

00:40:53.090 --> 00:40:55.460 align:middle line:84%
that I design really
approaching everybody

00:40:55.460 --> 00:40:58.220 align:middle line:84%
that comes to see me that
has a puzzle that we're

00:40:58.220 --> 00:40:59.270 align:middle line:90%
trying to solve.

00:40:59.270 --> 00:41:01.920 align:middle line:84%
And like I said, every
time we take a box

00:41:01.920 --> 00:41:03.930 align:middle line:84%
and we put the puzzle
pieces on the table,

00:41:03.930 --> 00:41:05.930 align:middle line:84%
we always look for the
four corner pieces first.

00:41:05.930 --> 00:41:08.200 align:middle line:84%
And then we start looking
for the edge pieces.

00:41:08.200 --> 00:41:10.700 align:middle line:84%
So the edges are what I call
the four pillars of the Freedom

00:41:10.700 --> 00:41:11.500 align:middle line:90%
Framework.

00:41:11.500 --> 00:41:14.480 align:middle line:84%
The first one is to
uncover the root causes.

00:41:14.480 --> 00:41:17.600 align:middle line:84%
And so we always have to look
at the root cause of anything.

00:41:17.600 --> 00:41:19.530 align:middle line:84%
And that will be
found in the body.

00:41:19.530 --> 00:41:22.100 align:middle line:84%
It'll be found in the mind,
and the heart, and the spirit,

00:41:22.100 --> 00:41:26.840 align:middle line:84%
and in the story I really listen
to how people tell their story.

00:41:26.840 --> 00:41:29.460 align:middle line:84%
If it's laden with
victimization,

00:41:29.460 --> 00:41:31.310 align:middle line:84%
I know we have to start
there, because it's

00:41:31.310 --> 00:41:33.240 align:middle line:90%
a disempowered way of being.

00:41:33.240 --> 00:41:36.655 align:middle line:84%
And I know that that hasn't
been digested properly yet.

00:41:36.655 --> 00:41:38.780 align:middle line:90%
And then the second--

00:41:38.780 --> 00:41:40.910 align:middle line:84%
well, to stick to
that first pillar

00:41:40.910 --> 00:41:42.890 align:middle line:84%
first, if we're
looking at the body,

00:41:42.890 --> 00:41:45.320 align:middle line:84%
that's functional medicine
laboratory testing.

00:41:45.320 --> 00:41:46.160 align:middle line:90%
It's genetics.

00:41:46.160 --> 00:41:47.750 align:middle line:90%
It's looking at your microbiome.

00:41:47.750 --> 00:41:49.310 align:middle line:84%
It's looking at
food sensitivities.

00:41:49.310 --> 00:41:52.160 align:middle line:84%
It's looking at your
hormones and your adrenals.

00:41:52.160 --> 00:41:53.300 align:middle line:90%
Who's living in your gut?

00:41:53.300 --> 00:41:55.070 align:middle line:84%
All of that is
part of that part.

00:41:55.070 --> 00:41:56.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The data.

00:41:56.180 --> 00:41:57.860 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: Really important.

00:41:57.860 --> 00:41:59.120 align:middle line:90%
So we're looking for those.

00:41:59.120 --> 00:42:02.210 align:middle line:84%
So that second
edge piece is going

00:42:02.210 --> 00:42:05.233 align:middle line:90%
to be to confront that data.

00:42:05.233 --> 00:42:06.650 align:middle line:84%
And that's going
to be your weight

00:42:06.650 --> 00:42:07.942 align:middle line:90%
that you get off of your scale.

00:42:07.942 --> 00:42:10.100 align:middle line:84%
It's going to be
your libido level.

00:42:10.100 --> 00:42:13.130 align:middle line:84%
I look at libido as
whole life vitality,

00:42:13.130 --> 00:42:15.590 align:middle line:90%
not necessarily sexual.

00:42:15.590 --> 00:42:18.620 align:middle line:84%
I'm looking at, are you
excited about the things

00:42:18.620 --> 00:42:19.760 align:middle line:90%
you've been excited about?

00:42:19.760 --> 00:42:21.260 align:middle line:90%
Or have you gone dull?

00:42:21.260 --> 00:42:23.278 align:middle line:90%
Is your light off?

00:42:23.278 --> 00:42:24.320 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Where is the joy?

00:42:24.320 --> 00:42:25.060 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: Exactly.

00:42:25.060 --> 00:42:26.430 align:middle line:84%
Or have you always
wanted to write a book,

00:42:26.430 --> 00:42:27.763 align:middle line:90%
but you're not getting anywhere?

00:42:27.763 --> 00:42:29.700 align:middle line:84%
You're just binge
watching Netflix.

00:42:29.700 --> 00:42:31.940 align:middle line:90%
So we're looking at that data.

00:42:31.940 --> 00:42:33.530 align:middle line:84%
We're looking at
the laboratory data

00:42:33.530 --> 00:42:38.030 align:middle line:84%
that we just talked about, your
quality of sleep, your mood.

00:42:38.030 --> 00:42:39.380 align:middle line:90%
That's all data.

00:42:39.380 --> 00:42:41.700 align:middle line:90%
It's feedback from your body.

00:42:41.700 --> 00:42:44.870 align:middle line:84%
Then the third is going
to be to really connect

00:42:44.870 --> 00:42:49.920 align:middle line:84%
the dots between that data
and your lifestyle choices.

00:42:49.920 --> 00:42:52.460 align:middle line:84%
So in other words, people
like to disconnect the fact

00:42:52.460 --> 00:42:54.500 align:middle line:84%
that they're
rewarding themselves

00:42:54.500 --> 00:42:57.710 align:middle line:84%
with the pastry and the fact
that they have joint pain.

00:42:57.710 --> 00:42:59.495 align:middle line:84%
They don't really
want to acknowledge

00:42:59.495 --> 00:43:00.620 align:middle line:90%
that those two go together.

00:43:00.620 --> 00:43:02.390 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Overeating
and weight gain.

00:43:02.390 --> 00:43:02.720 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: Exactly.

00:43:02.720 --> 00:43:03.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: There's a disconnect.

00:43:03.820 --> 00:43:04.620 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: Right.

00:43:04.620 --> 00:43:07.580 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes, like I said,
they're not overeating,

00:43:07.580 --> 00:43:10.070 align:middle line:84%
but there's some
bugs in the gut that

00:43:10.070 --> 00:43:13.430 align:middle line:84%
are creating the issue
with not losing weight.

00:43:13.430 --> 00:43:14.870 align:middle line:90%
Or there's a food sensitivity.

00:43:14.870 --> 00:43:18.170 align:middle line:84%
Maybe you're eating
a lot of coconut oil

00:43:18.170 --> 00:43:21.020 align:middle line:84%
and you're not genetically
able to manage that fat.

00:43:21.020 --> 00:43:23.130 align:middle line:84%
Or you have a food
sensitivity to it,

00:43:23.130 --> 00:43:27.020 align:middle line:84%
but you read somewhere that
good fats are good for you.

00:43:27.020 --> 00:43:29.490 align:middle line:84%
It's not true for
every single person.

00:43:29.490 --> 00:43:33.290 align:middle line:84%
So you have to actually connect
the dots between your data

00:43:33.290 --> 00:43:35.210 align:middle line:90%
and your lifestyle choices.

00:43:35.210 --> 00:43:36.440 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: This is so detailed.

00:43:36.440 --> 00:43:37.970 align:middle line:90%
I love this, yes.

00:43:37.970 --> 00:43:40.200 align:middle line:84%
>>EWERS: Because there is
never a one-size-fits-all.

00:43:40.200 --> 00:43:42.830 align:middle line:84%
