don't metabolize fats very

00:43:49.700 --> 00:43:50.600 align:middle line:90%
well.

00:43:50.600 --> 00:43:51.600 align:middle line:90%
It's really interesting.

00:43:51.600 --> 00:43:52.401 align:middle line:90%
I know.

00:43:52.401 --> 00:43:54.910 align:middle line:84%
And then if you look at it
from an Ayurvedic standpoint,

00:43:54.910 --> 00:43:58.790 align:middle line:84%
the kapha body type--
which I'm a pitta kapha.

00:43:58.790 --> 00:44:01.280 align:middle line:84%
I can't have that
much fat, either.

00:44:01.280 --> 00:44:04.460 align:middle line:84%
Sugar, fat, and processed
foods, and grains

00:44:04.460 --> 00:44:06.290 align:middle line:90%
actually make me gain weight.

00:44:06.290 --> 00:44:09.480 align:middle line:84%
So there's ever going to be
the same formula for everyone.

00:44:09.480 --> 00:44:11.980 align:middle line:84%
That's why this Freedom
Framework is so important.

00:44:11.980 --> 00:44:14.340 align:middle line:84%
And then the last edge
piece, the bottom of it,

00:44:14.340 --> 00:44:16.890 align:middle line:84%
is to create the life that you
want with intention instead

00:44:16.890 --> 00:44:18.480 align:middle line:84%
of what I call the
factory default

00:44:18.480 --> 00:44:20.160 align:middle line:90%
settings from childhood.

00:44:20.160 --> 00:44:22.980 align:middle line:84%
So instead of being
run by this idea

00:44:22.980 --> 00:44:25.500 align:middle line:84%
that I have to be
perfect to survive,

00:44:25.500 --> 00:44:28.560 align:middle line:84%
I have to reframe,
and reclaim my power,

00:44:28.560 --> 00:44:31.470 align:middle line:84%
and recreate the life that
I actually want to live,

00:44:31.470 --> 00:44:35.380 align:middle line:84%
not one that's driven from
the unconscious belief system.

00:44:35.380 --> 00:44:37.380 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's amazing
to think that success

00:44:37.380 --> 00:44:40.690 align:middle line:90%
comes from that trauma.

00:44:40.690 --> 00:44:41.770 align:middle line:90%
Isn't that interesting?

00:44:41.770 --> 00:44:42.570 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: Yes.

00:44:42.570 --> 00:44:45.210 align:middle line:84%
Success only comes
from that trauma

00:44:45.210 --> 00:44:47.347 align:middle line:90%
if you have digested it well.

00:44:47.347 --> 00:44:48.930 align:middle line:84%
Because otherwise,
you'll run yourself

00:44:48.930 --> 00:44:51.240 align:middle line:84%
into the ground trying
to be successful.

00:44:51.240 --> 00:44:53.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What is
healthy success then?

00:44:53.340 --> 00:44:56.280 align:middle line:84%
>>EWERS: Success where you
can enjoy your life still,

00:44:56.280 --> 00:44:59.190 align:middle line:84%
that you don't feel
overwhelmed, and overstressed.

00:44:59.190 --> 00:45:01.800 align:middle line:84%
And your children
look at you and don't

00:45:01.800 --> 00:45:03.180 align:middle line:90%
say, who are you again?

00:45:03.180 --> 00:45:04.380 align:middle line:90%
I don't recognize you.

00:45:04.380 --> 00:45:05.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:45:05.380 --> 00:45:06.180 align:middle line:90%
What are you doing?

00:45:06.180 --> 00:45:08.555 align:middle line:84%
>>EWERS: Exactly-- that
you've learned to balance.

00:45:08.555 --> 00:45:09.930 align:middle line:84%
And that's what
the whole Freedom

00:45:09.930 --> 00:45:12.760 align:middle line:84%
Framework is-- is learning
how to find that balance.

00:45:12.760 --> 00:45:14.970 align:middle line:84%
But you have to go
through those other three

00:45:14.970 --> 00:45:17.760 align:middle line:84%
before you can get to the create
the life you actually want.

00:45:17.760 --> 00:45:21.210 align:middle line:84%
Because the brain chemicals,
the messenger chemicals

00:45:21.210 --> 00:45:23.340 align:middle line:84%
from your brain called
neurotransmitters--

00:45:23.340 --> 00:45:25.290 align:middle line:84%
you have to measure
all these things,

00:45:25.290 --> 00:45:28.260 align:middle line:84%
see what you are doing to
make them go off the rails,

00:45:28.260 --> 00:45:31.230 align:middle line:84%
fix those before you
can get to that place

00:45:31.230 --> 00:45:35.580 align:middle line:84%
of nonjudgmental radical
acceptance, joy for the life

00:45:35.580 --> 00:45:37.110 align:middle line:90%
that you really want to lead.

00:45:37.110 --> 00:45:38.510 align:middle line:90%
We try to bypass all of that.

00:45:38.510 --> 00:45:40.260 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you also
relayed a lot of this

00:45:40.260 --> 00:45:41.580 align:middle line:90%
to archetypes, right?

00:45:41.580 --> 00:45:42.600 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: Yes.

00:45:42.600 --> 00:45:45.990 align:middle line:84%
So I've talked a little bit
about the victim archetype.

00:45:45.990 --> 00:45:48.540 align:middle line:84%
Archetypes are a
really amazing way

00:45:48.540 --> 00:45:54.150 align:middle line:84%
of understanding why you do
what you do in the world.

00:45:54.150 --> 00:45:57.000 align:middle line:84%
I use another framework
called the Enneagram.

00:45:57.000 --> 00:45:59.550 align:middle line:84%
And that's just a
way that your ego

00:45:59.550 --> 00:46:01.200 align:middle line:84%
created a strategy
to get its needs

00:46:01.200 --> 00:46:02.850 align:middle line:90%
met when you were a child.

00:46:02.850 --> 00:46:08.850 align:middle line:84%
They are the operating code on
your computer from childhood.

00:46:08.850 --> 00:46:10.650 align:middle line:84%
And you get to go
back, and you get

00:46:10.650 --> 00:46:12.690 align:middle line:84%
to upgrade that
once you discover

00:46:12.690 --> 00:46:17.880 align:middle line:84%
that it's there when you
have a fully-formed brain

00:46:17.880 --> 00:46:19.120 align:middle line:90%
in adulthood.

00:46:19.120 --> 00:46:22.442 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you go
into the feeling,

00:46:22.442 --> 00:46:23.400 align:middle line:90%
in all of the feelings.

00:46:23.400 --> 00:46:25.120 align:middle line:90%
And you sit with them.

00:46:25.120 --> 00:46:29.130 align:middle line:84%
And you then become aware of
what it is you're running,

00:46:29.130 --> 00:46:30.750 align:middle line:90%
whatever archetype that is.

00:46:30.750 --> 00:46:32.760 align:middle line:90%
What is the next step?

00:46:32.760 --> 00:46:33.650 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: It depends.

00:46:33.650 --> 00:46:36.040 align:middle line:84%
This, again, is not
going to be a cookbook

00:46:36.040 --> 00:46:37.320 align:middle line:90%
for every single person--

00:46:37.320 --> 00:46:39.480 align:middle line:90%
which is so frustrating.

00:46:39.480 --> 00:46:41.320 align:middle line:84%
I remember being in
my Ayurvedic training.

00:46:41.320 --> 00:46:43.275 align:middle line:84%
And I'd raise my
hand, ask my teacher,

00:46:43.275 --> 00:46:45.150 align:middle line:84%
so what if this, and
this, and this happened?

00:46:45.150 --> 00:46:48.920 align:middle line:84%
And every single time,
he would say, it depends.

00:46:48.920 --> 00:46:50.130 align:middle line:90%
And it is so true.

00:46:50.130 --> 00:46:56.160 align:middle line:84%
Because it depends on the body
type, and the past experiences,

00:46:56.160 --> 00:46:57.900 align:middle line:84%
and the current-day
health, and what's

00:46:57.900 --> 00:47:00.380 align:middle line:90%
going on for each person.

00:47:00.380 --> 00:47:02.970 align:middle line:84%
So I use these structures
to help people understand

00:47:02.970 --> 00:47:05.130 align:middle line:90%
where they are right now.

00:47:05.130 --> 00:47:07.650 align:middle line:84%
I do like to use Joseph
Campbell's hero's journey.

00:47:07.650 --> 00:47:09.480 align:middle line:90%
I call it the sheroe's journey--

00:47:09.480 --> 00:47:12.450 align:middle line:84%
TED Talk January,
2019 about this--

00:47:12.450 --> 00:47:18.330 align:middle line:84%
about using your trauma, your
disease, your challenge in life

00:47:18.330 --> 00:47:21.450 align:middle line:84%
that you might have thought
was very, very negative

00:47:21.450 --> 00:47:26.880 align:middle line:84%
and perhaps unfair to uplevel
your developmental state.

00:47:26.880 --> 00:47:30.180 align:middle line:84%
And the more that you do
that-- there are developmental

00:47:30.180 --> 00:47:32.460 align:middle line:84%
states that we
accelerate through.

00:47:32.460 --> 00:47:33.570 align:middle line:90%
And they're always hard.

00:47:33.570 --> 00:47:35.740 align:middle line:84%
It's hard to go from
one to the next.

00:47:35.740 --> 00:47:38.520 align:middle line:84%
And you can use the hero's
journey to understand it.

00:47:38.520 --> 00:47:39.900 align:middle line:90%
You have a call to action.

00:47:39.900 --> 00:47:42.900 align:middle line:84%
Rheumatoid arthritis
was one for me.

00:47:42.900 --> 00:47:46.410 align:middle line:84%
Then you get to either heed
the call or reject the call.

00:47:46.410 --> 00:47:49.063 align:middle line:84%
If I ignore it, it will
keep moving through my body.

00:47:49.063 --> 00:47:51.480 align:middle line:84%
I'll get worse, and worse, and
worse with twisted fingers.

00:47:51.480 --> 00:47:54.210 align:middle line:84%
I was already starting
to get them twisted,

00:47:54.210 --> 00:47:57.660 align:middle line:84%
unless I accept the call,
heed it as something

00:47:57.660 --> 00:47:59.550 align:middle line:84%
that I need to go learn
some new information,

00:47:59.550 --> 00:48:01.860 align:middle line:90%
find a mentor for that.

00:48:01.860 --> 00:48:04.110 align:middle line:90%
So I found a mentor.

00:48:04.110 --> 00:48:05.760 align:middle line:84%
Then you get this
new information

00:48:05.760 --> 00:48:08.140 align:middle line:84%
that is coming from
the unknown world.

00:48:08.140 --> 00:48:11.670 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know anything
about herbs, Ayurveda, yoga.

00:48:11.670 --> 00:48:13.740 align:middle line:90%
I knew nothing about therapy.

00:48:13.740 --> 00:48:15.437 align:middle line:90%
I'd never been to therapy.

00:48:15.437 --> 00:48:17.520 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know any of the
stuff I talk about today.

00:48:17.520 --> 00:48:19.470 align:middle line:90%
That was the unknown world.

00:48:19.470 --> 00:48:20.730 align:middle line:90%
You get that information.

00:48:20.730 --> 00:48:23.250 align:middle line:84%
And then you have to go
into your innermost cave

00:48:23.250 --> 00:48:24.630 align:middle line:90%
and integrate it.

00:48:24.630 --> 00:48:29.010 align:middle line:84%
How does this fit into my life
where I am on my path today?

00:48:29.010 --> 00:48:30.030 align:middle line:90%
Then you come out.

00:48:30.030 --> 00:48:32.130 align:middle line:84%
And this is what really
makes people mad.

00:48:32.130 --> 00:48:34.560 align:middle line:84%
Life will start to
offer you experiences

00:48:34.560 --> 00:48:35.795 align:middle line:90%
where you get to practice.

00:48:35.795 --> 00:48:36.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Found you.

00:48:36.250 --> 00:48:36.910 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:48:36.910 --> 00:48:37.590 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:48:37.590 --> 00:48:39.298 align:middle line:84%
>>EWERS: And then when
you get to mastery

00:48:39.298 --> 00:48:41.490 align:middle line:84%
of that-- which means you
have to practice it over,

00:48:41.490 --> 00:48:42.532 align:middle line:90%
and over, and over again.

00:48:42.532 --> 00:48:44.220 align:middle line:90%
And sometimes, you'll fail.

00:48:44.220 --> 00:48:46.390 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes,
you'll be successful.

00:48:46.390 --> 00:48:51.245 align:middle line:84%
Then you actually emerge into
your next state of development.

00:48:51.245 --> 00:48:52.620 align:middle line:84%
And you come back,
you could say,

00:48:52.620 --> 00:48:55.200 align:middle line:84%
resurrected as an
oracle or a teacher.

00:48:55.200 --> 00:48:57.810 align:middle line:84%
And you get to share that
now with your community.

00:48:57.810 --> 00:49:00.270 align:middle line:84%
But the thing that really
makes people mad-- and this

00:49:00.270 --> 00:49:02.520 align:middle line:84%
is what I see in my medical
practice all the time.

00:49:02.520 --> 00:49:04.350 align:middle line:90%
And I teach a lot of students.

00:49:04.350 --> 00:49:07.270 align:middle line:84%
They get so mad when
they have overcome,

00:49:07.270 --> 00:49:08.912 align:middle line:84%
and they've come out
on the other end,

00:49:08.912 --> 00:49:10.370 align:middle line:84%
and they've learned
this new stuff,

00:49:10.370 --> 00:49:13.040 align:middle line:84%
and they've gotten to this
new developmental level.

00:49:13.040 --> 00:49:15.740 align:middle line:84%
But then they get
another call to action.

00:49:15.740 --> 00:49:18.090 align:middle line:90%
But that's the cycles of life.

00:49:18.090 --> 00:49:19.460 align:middle line:90%
That's the way it works.

00:49:19.460 --> 00:49:21.020 align:middle line:84%
We move from one
cycle to the next.

00:49:21.020 --> 00:49:23.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do we ever stop
those call to actions?

00:49:23.270 --> 00:49:24.380 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: Then you die.

00:49:24.380 --> 00:49:24.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:49:24.600 --> 00:49:25.670 align:middle line:90%
So it's part of life.

00:49:25.670 --> 00:49:26.920 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: This is part of life.

00:49:26.920 --> 00:49:29.048 align:middle line:84%
And if we understand--
and I always say,

00:49:29.048 --> 00:49:31.340 align:middle line:84%
one of the biggest things
I've learned in this lifetime

00:49:31.340 --> 00:49:34.920 align:middle line:84%
is that all unhappiness comes
from unmet expectations.

00:49:34.920 --> 00:49:37.100 align:middle line:84%
And if you expect
that that's going

00:49:37.100 --> 00:49:41.790 align:middle line:84%
to happen, then when it happens,
you're not so mad about it.

00:49:41.790 --> 00:49:42.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Good point.

00:49:42.590 --> 00:49:43.390 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: Yeah.

00:49:43.390 --> 00:49:45.190 align:middle line:84%
So I went from RA
to breast cancer.

00:49:45.190 --> 00:49:46.500 align:middle line:90%
But I'd already learned this.

00:49:46.500 --> 00:49:47.300 align:middle line:90%
And it was like--

00:49:47.300 --> 00:49:48.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, my god.

00:49:48.100 --> 00:49:49.940 align:middle line:84%
>>EWERS: --OK, now I
know what I need to do.

00:49:49.940 --> 00:49:52.490 align:middle line:84%
And I was able to
cure it naturally.

00:49:52.490 --> 00:49:54.410 align:middle line:90%
Within a month, it was gone.

00:49:54.410 --> 00:49:57.350 align:middle line:84%
And that was a
whole other story.

00:49:57.350 --> 00:49:58.150 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:49:58.150 --> 00:49:59.692 align:middle line:84%
>>EWERS: But I wasn't
angry about it.

00:49:59.692 --> 00:50:02.120 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't all the things
I had been with RA.

00:50:02.120 --> 00:50:06.230 align:middle line:84%
And so if we can learn
that this is part of life,

00:50:06.230 --> 00:50:08.660 align:middle line:84%
it's part of the
cycles of life--

00:50:08.660 --> 00:50:11.060 align:middle line:90%
spring follows winter.

00:50:11.060 --> 00:50:12.147 align:middle line:90%
Summer follows spring.

00:50:12.147 --> 00:50:12.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:50:12.980 --> 00:50:15.415 align:middle line:84%
>>EWERS: And nature shows
us this all the time.

00:50:15.415 --> 00:50:16.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you
don't really need

00:50:16.790 --> 00:50:21.038 align:middle line:84%
to judge yourself for the drama
and, like you said, the crises.

00:50:21.038 --> 00:50:22.580 align:middle line:84%
>>EWERS: I've had
functional medicine

00:50:22.580 --> 00:50:24.200 align:middle line:84%
doctors come to
me in my practice,

00:50:24.200 --> 00:50:25.820 align:middle line:90%
and they've had cancer.

00:50:25.820 --> 00:50:27.217 align:middle line:90%
And they keep it a secret.

00:50:27.217 --> 00:50:29.300 align:middle line:84%
They won't talk about it,
because they're ashamed.

00:50:29.300 --> 00:50:30.967 align:middle line:84%
Because if they were
walking their talk,

00:50:30.967 --> 00:50:32.330 align:middle line:90%
they wouldn't get sick.

00:50:32.330 --> 00:50:34.065 align:middle line:90%
That is so untrue.

00:50:34.065 --> 00:50:35.690 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's being
hard on ourselves.

00:50:35.690 --> 00:50:37.940 align:middle line:84%
>>EWERS: Well,
plus, it's untrue.

00:50:37.940 --> 00:50:40.670 align:middle line:84%
You can do and
control what you can.

00:50:40.670 --> 00:50:43.430 align:middle line:90%
But life is actually in control.

00:50:43.430 --> 00:50:44.467 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:50:44.467 --> 00:50:45.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's going to take over.

00:50:45.800 --> 00:50:49.070 align:middle line:84%
>>EWERS: And so, if you
expect and you understand

00:50:49.070 --> 00:50:51.170 align:middle line:84%
that, then when you get
your next challenge,

00:50:51.170 --> 00:50:53.330 align:middle line:84%
it's not going to be
something you expect.

00:50:53.330 --> 00:50:56.210 align:middle line:84%
And it's going to be something
that's going to challenge you.

00:50:56.210 --> 00:50:58.760 align:middle line:84%
Then you can say, oh,
here's the next one.

00:50:58.760 --> 00:51:00.260 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you have
a way for people

00:51:00.260 --> 00:51:03.580 align:middle line:84%
to get in touch with this
system, and the ACE testing,

00:51:03.580 --> 00:51:04.380 align:middle line:90%
and so forth?

00:51:04.380 --> 00:51:06.080 align:middle line:84%
How do people take
it to the next level

00:51:06.080 --> 00:51:07.430 align:middle line:84%
if they're really
lit up right now?

00:51:07.430 --> 00:51:08.810 align:middle line:84%
>>EWERS: "Solving the
Autoimmune Puzzle"

00:51:08.810 --> 00:51:09.990 align:middle line:90%
is a great way to start.

00:51:09.990 --> 00:51:15.020 align:middle line:84%
That's my book that I wrote all
this in, the Freedom Framework.

00:51:15.020 --> 00:51:18.830 align:middle line:84%
And "Solving the Autoimmune
Puzzle" has worksheets in it.

00:51:18.830 --> 00:51:21.420 align:middle line:84%
You can digest it
at your own pace.

00:51:21.420 --> 00:51:24.110 align:middle line:10%
And then I also have a
program called You Unbroken

00:51:24.110 --> 00:51:26.000 align:middle line:10%
on my website, on drkeesha.com.

00:51:26.000 --> 00:51:30.170 align:middle line:10%
And it's trauma that
you never thought maybe

00:51:30.170 --> 00:51:32.430 align:middle line:10%
you needed to heal--
it's how to do that.

00:51:32.430 --> 00:51:34.470 align:middle line:84%
And I have hard stops
in it, where I say,

00:51:34.470 --> 00:51:36.690 align:middle line:84%
OK, if you can't
get past this point,

00:51:36.690 --> 00:51:38.540 align:middle line:90%
you need to go borrow a brain.

00:51:38.540 --> 00:51:40.703 align:middle line:84%
Here's the kind of
therapist you need to find.

00:51:40.703 --> 00:51:42.620 align:middle line:84%
And then I want you to
shop for your therapist

00:51:42.620 --> 00:51:45.290 align:middle line:84%
the way you would
shop for shoes.

00:51:45.290 --> 00:51:46.515 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Try them on.

00:51:46.515 --> 00:51:48.140 align:middle line:84%
>>EWERS: You can't
go into a shoe store

00:51:48.140 --> 00:51:51.500 align:middle line:84%
and say, I want a pair of tall,
over-the-knee brown boots.

00:51:51.500 --> 00:51:53.930 align:middle line:84%
And then you find that
you find one pair,

00:51:53.930 --> 00:51:55.010 align:middle line:90%
and it pinches your toe.

00:51:55.010 --> 00:51:57.230 align:middle line:84%
You don't walk out of the
shoe store without shoes

00:51:57.230 --> 00:51:59.150 align:middle line:84%
on and say, well, shoes
don't work for me--

00:51:59.150 --> 00:52:01.940 align:middle line:84%
which is what people
do around therapy.

00:52:01.940 --> 00:52:04.340 align:middle line:84%
And so you have to say,
OK, I have to keep looking.

00:52:04.340 --> 00:52:05.423 align:middle line:90%
I really want these boots.

00:52:05.423 --> 00:52:06.840 align:middle line:84%
So I'm going to
go somewhere else.

00:52:06.840 --> 00:52:08.310 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to keep
trying them on.

00:52:08.310 --> 00:52:10.310 align:middle line:84%
And you also have to know
that talk therapy just

00:52:10.310 --> 00:52:12.190 align:middle line:90%
does not work.

00:52:12.190 --> 00:52:13.910 align:middle line:90%
It does not work.

00:52:13.910 --> 00:52:15.960 align:middle line:84%
You can do that
with a girlfriend.

00:52:15.960 --> 00:52:17.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What is the best kind?

00:52:17.210 --> 00:52:18.010 align:middle line:90%
What does work?

00:52:18.010 --> 00:52:19.850 align:middle line:84%
>>EWERS: Trauma
release therapy comes

00:52:19.850 --> 00:52:21.590 align:middle line:90%
in several different packages.

00:52:21.590 --> 00:52:24.920 align:middle line:84%
And each therapist that
knows that format of therapy

00:52:24.920 --> 00:52:27.300 align:middle line:84%
is not maybe going
