00:53:39.470 --> 00:53:42.890 align:middle line:84%
What is a healthy
sexual relationship?

00:53:42.890 --> 00:53:44.330 align:middle line:90%
I know you get asked this a lot.

00:53:44.330 --> 00:53:45.130 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: Yeah.

00:53:45.130 --> 00:53:46.850 align:middle line:84%
It's such a good
question, because--

00:53:46.850 --> 00:53:49.290 align:middle line:84%
you're going to hear me
say the same thing again--

00:53:49.290 --> 00:53:50.960 align:middle line:90%
it depends.

00:53:50.960 --> 00:53:53.210 align:middle line:84%
A healthy sexual
relationship is going

00:53:53.210 --> 00:53:55.500 align:middle line:84%
to be one where there's
healthy communication.

00:53:55.500 --> 00:53:57.620 align:middle line:84%
So I always say that
really fantastic,

00:53:57.620 --> 00:54:00.560 align:middle line:84%
scrape-you-off-the-walls sex
comes from really fantastic

00:54:00.560 --> 00:54:02.930 align:middle line:84%
scrape-you-off-the-walls
communication.

00:54:02.930 --> 00:54:07.460 align:middle line:84%
Women tend to really want their
partner to read their minds.

00:54:07.460 --> 00:54:08.470 align:middle line:90%
They really say--

00:54:08.470 --> 00:54:09.580 align:middle line:90%
I hear this all the time--

00:54:09.580 --> 00:54:11.590 align:middle line:84%
well, if he or she
loved me, then they'd

00:54:11.590 --> 00:54:13.420 align:middle line:84%
be able to know
what makes me tick.

00:54:13.420 --> 00:54:16.070 align:middle line:84%
And that is really
radically unfair.

00:54:16.070 --> 00:54:17.890 align:middle line:90%
That is not accurate.

00:54:17.890 --> 00:54:22.300 align:middle line:84%
And we have these
background experiences that

00:54:22.300 --> 00:54:23.740 align:middle line:90%
make us who we are as adults.

00:54:23.740 --> 00:54:26.810 align:middle line:84%
And we're not always
able to read minds.

00:54:26.810 --> 00:54:28.330 align:middle line:90%
In fact, that's pretty unusual.

00:54:28.330 --> 00:54:31.070 align:middle line:84%
And it should not be an
expectation from your partner.

00:54:31.070 --> 00:54:34.090 align:middle line:84%
And so I always tell women,
if you really want fantastic,

00:54:34.090 --> 00:54:36.400 align:middle line:84%
scrape-you-off-the-wall
sex with a partner,

00:54:36.400 --> 00:54:38.980 align:middle line:84%
then that means you have to
be able to know your own body

00:54:38.980 --> 00:54:42.940 align:middle line:84%
first and communicate how to
get around that body for someone

00:54:42.940 --> 00:54:43.970 align:middle line:90%
else.

00:54:43.970 --> 00:54:46.270 align:middle line:84%
And so that means being able
to ask for what you want.

00:54:46.270 --> 00:54:47.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, and receive.

00:54:47.770 --> 00:54:50.410 align:middle line:84%
>>EWERS: And that's, oftentimes,
a big barrier for women--

00:54:50.410 --> 00:54:53.870 align:middle line:84%
is receiving, and saying,
and articulating specifically

00:54:53.870 --> 00:54:54.670 align:middle line:90%
what they want.

00:54:54.670 --> 00:54:56.680 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yes, rather
than just pleasing.

00:54:56.680 --> 00:54:58.900 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: Right, exactly.

00:54:58.900 --> 00:55:01.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Is there
another way to--

00:55:01.810 --> 00:55:04.210 align:middle line:84%
you say, what's in your
