00:55:09.750 --> 00:55:12.020 align:middle line:84%
>>EWERS: No, what's in your
head does go to your bud.

00:55:12.020 --> 00:55:14.980 align:middle line:84%
And I will work with
a single person--

00:55:14.980 --> 00:55:16.900 align:middle line:84%
I don't mean
non-partner, but I mean

00:55:16.900 --> 00:55:18.910 align:middle line:84%
an individual in my
practice for a little while.

00:55:18.910 --> 00:55:22.480 align:middle line:84%
And then I'll start seeing,
it's always a systems problem.

00:55:22.480 --> 00:55:25.460 align:middle line:84%
If a child is having a
problem and needs therapy,

00:55:25.460 --> 00:55:27.280 align:middle line:90%
it's a systems problem.

00:55:27.280 --> 00:55:28.120 align:middle line:90%
It's a dynamic--

00:55:28.120 --> 00:55:28.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Big picture.

00:55:28.600 --> 00:55:29.808 align:middle line:10%
>>EWERS: --inside the couple.

00:55:29.808 --> 00:55:32.780 align:middle line:10%
If one of them is having an
issue, it's a systems problem.

00:55:32.780 --> 00:55:34.420 align:middle line:10%
And so then I always,
at some point,

00:55:34.420 --> 00:55:36.340 align:middle line:10%
pull the couple together.

00:55:36.340 --> 00:55:38.470 align:middle line:90%
And we start working on that.

00:55:38.470 --> 00:55:40.660 align:middle line:84%
And then usually,
this other individual

00:55:40.660 --> 00:55:42.760 align:middle line:90%
has to do some work, too.

00:55:42.760 --> 00:55:45.430 align:middle line:84%
In order to uplevel,
you've got to tear apart

00:55:45.430 --> 00:55:47.380 align:middle line:84%
the scaffolding and
the foundation that

00:55:47.380 --> 00:55:48.795 align:middle line:90%
didn't work, and rebuild it.

00:55:48.795 --> 00:55:49.670 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And cover it.

00:55:49.670 --> 00:55:50.050 align:middle line:90%
>>EWERS: Yeah.

00:55:50.050 --> 00:55:51.425 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I always
asked my guests,

00:55:51.425 --> 00:55:53.870 align:middle line:84%
